# Active Directory Group Membership Management

## Overview

This lab demonstrates how to create and manage Active Directory Security Groups to simplify permission management in an enterprise environment.

Rather than assigning permissions directly to individual users, organizations use Security Groups to efficiently manage access to shared resources, printers, applications, and administrative privileges.

---

## Objective

- Create department-based Security Groups
- Add users to the appropriate groups
- Verify group membership
- Understand the relationship between Organizational Units (OUs) and Security Groups
- Understand Microsoft's best practice for assigning permissions

---

## Lab Environment

- Windows Server 2022
- Windows 11 Client
- Active Directory Domain Services
- Group Policy Management
- VMware Workstation
- Domain: CHARLYCYBER.LOCAL

